fields.gigDesc: Top drawer of the wardrobe is organized with inspection items IAW SCLA. Hats are displayed in proper order and are clean.
Bed is made IAW SCLA (2 sheets, gray blanket, green blanket). Bed sheets are tight and clean.
Pillow and green blanket folded neatly and correctly. Area beneath and behind bed is generally clean and organized.
Bureau is neat and organized.
Shoes organized and displayed as worn (# of shoes IAW SCLA; broom and dust pan stored neatly; top shelf clean.
Desk area generally organized and clean. Books on shelf are organized in descending height order.
Desk area generally organized and clean. Books on shelf are organized in descending height order.
Unauthorized devices (WAP, X-Box, etc…) connected to network
Drawers are closed, clean and organized neatly.
All HVIs secured.
Laundry stored in green bag, closed with the opening facing up. Towel and washcloth folded IAW SCLA.
Medicine cabinet arranged neatly with no grime or smudges on shelves. Area beneath sink is neat and organized.
All items on desk and shelves are dusted, arranged neatly and do not detract from the military appearance of the room.
Nametapes are placed correctly and IAW SCLA (door, desk, bookshelf, bed, rifle rack, inside sink cabinet, top right of bureau, and wardrobe).
Area is generally clean and swept. If Firstie, saber present with crest facing out. If underclassman, rifles are secured.
Shoes and boots are aligned correctly, displayed as worn (applies if stored in wardrobe) and clean and serviceable.
Sink, faucet, mirror and counter top free of any grime or smudges; stopper pulled up and sink dry (for AMI only).
Closed door or sleeping during AMI
Floor is swept and all surfaces clean—creating a professional military appearance.
Trash can is clean with minimal garbage (<25% full). If appliances are displayed on counter, they must be IAW SCLA.

All uniforms hanging in wardrobe IAW SCLA, (displayed as worn except for duplicates). Hangers canted towards the right and evenly spaced throughout wardrobe (only wooden hangers). Number of civilian shirts/items is IAW with class privileges.
